tory that actually is a symlink to the root of a dataset gets the `FileNotInRepositoryError` finger\r\n\r\n```\r\nPath outside repository: /tmp/datalad_temp_test_symlinked_relpath_dvazitr/linked\r\n[Errno None] : Path outside repository: /tmp/datalad_temp_test_symlinked_relpath_dvazitr/linked: '/tmp/datalad_temp_test_syml\r\n```\r\n\r\n(yes, you see that correct: the path in question is identical to the repo base path).\r\n\r\nThe reason is the code in _normalize_paths():\r\n```\r\npath = opj(realpath(dirname(path)), basename(path))\r\n```\r\n\r\nOnly the `dirname` portion of the path is resolved, but the symlink is the final portion. The backdrop for this failure is:\r\n\r\n```\r\ndef test_symlinked_relpath(path):\r\n    # initially ran into on OSX https://github.com/datalad/datalad/issues/2406\r\n    os.makedirs(opj(path, \"origin\"))\r\n    dspath = opj(path, \"linked\")\r\n    os.symlink('origin', dspath)\r\n    ds = Dataset(dspath).create()\r\n ```\r\n\r\nWe don't see this in master ATM, because about a dozen layers before it wrangle the incoming path in a way that shadows the issues.\r\n\r\nBehavior was introduced in https://github.com/datalad/datalad/commit/a0fb77c323f7395c36755a378ad30bd9d8db2cd8 to prevent resolving symlinks into an annex.", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "h